04/11/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The mayor of Kerbala, Akram al-Yassri praised the contribution the Bulgarian contingent in his town has made to security and democracy Monday (3 October).
Visiting Sofia at the invitation of Foreign Minster Solomon Passy, al-Yassri said Kerbalans view the Bulgarian troops as close friends who have helped rebuild schools, hospitals and roads.
In other news Monday, Bulgaria and Russia opened another round of bilateral political consultations in Moscow.
The delegations exchanged views on NATO and EU integration processes, and the need for broader co-operation in terms of culture and education.
(bTV, Trud, 24 Chassa - 04/11/03;
BTA, BNT, Nova TV - 03/11/03)
